headline: TI introduces the world's smallest MCU, enabling innovation in the tiniest of applications
summary: Texas Instruments (TI) (Nasdaq: TXN) today introduced the world's smallest MCU, expanding its comprehensive Arm® Cortex®-M0+ MSPM0 MCU portfolio. Measuring only 1.38mm2, about the size of a black pepper flake, the wafer chip-scale package (WCSP) for the MSPM0C1104 MCU enables designers to optimize board space in applications such as medical wearables and personal electronics, without compromising performance.
